Testing STICS on Auzeville data

R. VEZY

14 juin, 2018

Introduction

An experimentation was set on the fields of INRA at Auzeville for the years 2006, 2007, 2012 and 2013. The experimentation consisted in evaluating Wheat and Pea crops in:
* sole crops at full density (resp. 280 and 60) or at half density (resp. 140 and 30)
* mixed crops at half density (resp. 140 and 30)
for different levels of nitrogen fertilization: 0, 100 and 180 kg ha-1 year-1.
The STICS model was run on the 5 types of crops (sole*4 + mixed) and the evaluation of the model is made on different observed and simulated variables. Some are measured at field level, and some for each species in the field.

Data import

The simulations are made and imported using the sticRs package. For exemple, the mixed crop simulations are run and imported using the stics_eval function (see code).

library(sticRs)
sim_Wheat_Pea= 
  stics_eval(dir.orig = file.path(Source_dir,"IC_Wheat_Pea"), 
             dir.targ = file.path(Simulation_dir,"IC_Wheat_Pea"),
             stics = Sics_exe, 
             obs_name =  obs_names[["Mixed"]],
             Out_var = c(Out_var_plant,Out_var_plot),plot_it = F)$outputs

Wheat in sole crop

STICS was run for a wheat in sole crop

sim_Wheat$gg_object+labs(title= "STICS evaluation on a wheat sole crop")

Wheat in self-intercroping (Wheat-Wheat)

STICS was run for wheat in intercropping with wheat. This is a test to evaluate the model response using a zero hypothesis for intercropping (self-intercroping). Ideally, the model gives the closest outputs compared to a run in sole crop.

The wheat planting density was set to half the full density (=140), and the observations in the plots are from an experimentation in full density of a sole crop. The observed above-ground dry mass masec was divided by two fo comparison, because we expect half the total observed masec for the principal wheat, and half the masec for the associated wheat.

Evaluation at field scale

Here is an evaluation of the STICS model using measurements at field scale:

plot_output_plant(x= sim_Wheat_Wheat,Title= "STICS evaluation on wheat self-intercropping")

Evaluation for each crop “species” from the same field

Here is an evaluation of the STICS model using measurements at field scale:

sim_Wheat_Wheat[["Vars"]]= Out_var_plant
do.call(sticRs::plot_output,sim_Wheat_Wheat)

Pea in self-intercropping (Pea-Pea)

STICS was run for pea in intercropping with pea. This is a test to evaluate the model response using a zero hypothesis for intercropping (self-intercroping). Ideally, the model gives the closest outputs compared to a run in sole crop.

The pea planting density was set to half the full density (=30), and the observations in the plots are from an experimentation in full density of a sole crop. The observed above-ground dry mass masec was divided by two fo comparison, because we expect half the total observed masec for the principal pea, and half the masec for the associated pea.
